editorialSummary.text: Trendy library-style restaurant dishing up small plates, housemade pasta, sandwiches & cocktails.

originalText.text:
I saw some low rated reviews and decided to write a review.

I’ve been going Anything at all for several years now. There are ups and downs in taste and service. I mostly had good experiences though.

Food:
I figured the taste is different in a good way and a bad way depending on the time I dine in. They try to use seasonal ingredients and it changes the vegetable and fruit components on the dish. I think this is good try and not a major change of the main flavor.
I assume there are different kitchen staffs and differently cook meats..? Sometimes, proteins are burnt till taste bitter. Especially, on my last visit, I only tasted bitterness from my sandwich. I think the consistency of taste is really important. Like, I expect to have the same burger whenever I go to this place but it is disappointing when it doesn’t taste the same.

Service:
Most of staffs are friendly and willing to explain things according to customer’s needs. But, I had some staffs who didn’t explain delay on the food or rush out to eat or not getting what’s asked for.

Overall, I had better experience brunch than dinner. Apparently, their burger is my and my husband’s favorite burger in New York City. We always bring people when someone visits us. 70% was successful. Everyone was impressed with the taste, atmosphere, and service. However, we sometimes regretted bringing people and having such an important occasion here due to the inconsistencies I mentioned.

As if they can keep the consistency of food and services, I can say they have beautiful aesthetics and atmosphere. I love how their food is organic and high quality.

originalText.text: Located at 22 N Loop Rd, New York, NY 10044, Anything At All is a charming venue that offers a warm and inviting atmosphere. I discovered this hidden gem through a recommendation from the hotel where I was staying, and it turned out to be a wonderful way to start my day.  The area surrounding Anything At All is serene and picturesque. Nestled in a quiet neighborhood, it provides a welcome escape from the bustling city. The peaceful surroundings create a pleasant ambiance that complements the cozy atmosphere of the venue.  Upon entering, I was greeted by friendly staff who exudes warmth and hospitality. Their attentive service made me feel right at home. The pleasant interactions and promptness added to the overall positive experience.  Now, let's talk about the highlight of the morning—the food! originalText.text: I stopped in here yesterday for a cocktail with my girlfriend. We stopped at the bar and despite there being only 2 other patrons it took over 5 minutes for the bartender to notice our existence. The drinks were actually great and we enjoyed them on the patio. When we went to pay however it somehow took 15 minutes to just take my card. The woman next to me told me I have just walked out, and I SHOULD HAVE because when I finally received my bill for 2 cocktails the staff had already entered a mandatory 20% tip. Where do they get off. Beware of coming here, if the zombie staff manage to actually notice you, they will rob you!

originalText.text: Slow service and at times bizarre! But the food was always delicious! Had breakfast, lunch and dinner here while staying at the Graduate for 5 nights. The burger is so so so good!!!  The atmosphere is cool, the big windows and the books and the danish modern/mid century modern decor is stylish and comfortable. Didn’t know until the last night I stayed they have dessert!
